Task MUST complete:
You are modifying Vue 3 components in a restaurant POS project to add multi-language support using vue-i18n. The project has vue-i18n configured with `globalInjection: true`, so `$t()` is available in all templates. Translation keys are under the `customer` namespace.

For script-level text, add `import { useI18n } from 'vue-i18n';` and `const { t } = useI18n();` (or `const { t, locale } = useI18n();` if you need locale), then use `t('key')` instead of hardcoded strings. Read each file FIRST, then use the `replace` tool.

=== FILE 1: E:\Công ty\Task\260\Product\src\views\customer\OrderHistory.vue ===

Template changes (replace Vietnamese text with $t() calls):
- 'Lịch sử gọi món' → {{ $t('customer.orderHistory.title') }}
- 'Theo dõi chi tiết món ăn đang chuẩn bị và hóa đơn tại bàn' → {{ $t('customer.orderHistory.subtitle') }}
